headline: Big Bank earnings, Fed commentary, tax deadline: What to Watch
summary: Yahoo Finance host Josh Lipton highlights what to watch on Tuesday, April 15. Earnings reports are expected from Johnson & Johnson (JNJ), Albertsons (ACI), and United Airlines (UAL), as well as major banks like Bank of America (BAC) and Citi (C). Fresh Federal Reserve commentary is coming as Fed Governor Lisa Cook is set to speak. The deadline to file 2024 federal income tax returns is also on Tuesday. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: Pfizer hits setback in obesity drug race as GLP-1 trial halts
summary: Pfizer (PFE) is ending a late-stage trial of its once-daily GLP-1 pill, Danuglipron, after a participant experienced a liver injury. Yahoo Finance Senior Reporter Anjalee Khemlani joins Market Domination Overtime to break down the details, as well as preview what to watch as Johnson & Johnson (JNJ) prepares to report earnings. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: Johnson & Johnson Is Beating the Market. Legal Troubles Continue as Earnings Arrive.
summary: Johnson & Johnson  is scheduled to report its  fiscal first-quarter earnings before markets open on Tuesday, but the company has bigger hurdles to clear than meeting Wall Street’s expectations.  While shares have lagged behind the  for the past three years, J&J remains up 6.7% in 2025 versus the broader market’s 8.1% decline.  Part of the appeal is J&J’s resilience in the face of a potential recession.
